23:49.761 --> 23:51.729
So what are we doing here?

23:51.797 --> 23:53.788
I think they call it a Hail Mary.

23:55.867 --> 23:58.301
We want justice! We want justice!

24:04.376 --> 24:06.003
<i>As-salaam alaikum.</i>

24:06.077 --> 24:07.567
<i>Wa alaikum assalam.</i>

24:07.646 --> 24:10.638
- My name is Carrie.
- I know who you are.

24:10.715 --> 24:13.047
May I come in?

24:13.118 --> 24:15.052
I need to speak with your husband.

24:24.896 --> 24:26.887
Please, have some tea.

24:32.204 --> 24:34.399
I'm sorry. This isn't easy.

24:34.473 --> 24:36.100
I understand.

24:37.476 --> 24:39.501
Imam, I've done my research.

24:39.578 --> 24:41.546
I know of your work in the community-

24:41.613 --> 24:45.709
the woman's refuge you run with Father
Rose from Saint Agnes down the street.

24:45.784 --> 24:49.083
I have no doubt you and I
want the same thing.

24:49.154 --> 24:52.954
- Which is a better world.
- And a better America.

24:55.327 --> 24:59.627
If there's another terrorist attack,
this country is primed to turn on itself.

24:59.698 --> 25:02.223
You and I both know
we're halfway there already.

25:03.969 --> 25:06.767
But if an attack happens
that can be traced back to information...

25:06.838 --> 25:09.932
that you chose to withhold
when you were given the chance...

25:12.344 --> 25:13.834
the mosque...

25:15.113 --> 25:18.048
this community that you worked
so hard to build-

25:19.885 --> 25:22.046
they'll put a match to it all.

25:25.724 --> 25:28.989
Our only hope- and it's a good one-

25:29.060 --> 25:33.121
is that people like us put our heads
together and help each other.

25:33.198 --> 25:35.894
Now, I need to find Tom Walker.

25:38.637 --> 25:40.400
Will you help me?

25:43.842 --> 25:48.142
I pray what you say about another attack
on America is wrong.

25:48.213 --> 25:51.444
But you're right.
It takes more than just prayer.

25:51.516 --> 25:53.450
We have to help each other.

25:55.320 --> 25:57.345
Action speaks louder than words...

25:57.422 --> 26:00.118
yet so far you've done nothing but talk.

26:01.493 --> 26:03.290
What were you expecting?

26:03.361 --> 26:05.852
It's very simple- truth.

26:08.233 --> 26:11.202
Two people were tragically caught
between a terrorist suspect...

26:11.269 --> 26:14.170
and those whose job it is
to stop more attacks on America.

26:14.239 --> 26:16.673
That is the truth.

26:17.909 --> 26:20.173
I know you know Walker.

26:24.282 --> 26:26.614
Please.

26:30.855 --> 26:33.881
If I say I have no information,
I have no information.

26:33.959 --> 26:35.449
I'm sorry.

26:52.744 --> 26:54.541
In case you reconsider.

26:58.984 --> 27:00.645
Thank you for the tea.

27:00.719 --> 27:02.209
<i>As-salaam alaikum.</i>

27:07.559 --> 27:10.585
We want justice! We want justice!

27:15.700 --> 27:17.395
How'd it go?

27:19.304 --> 27:23.035
The F.B.I. Better fucking find Walker.
That's all I can say.

28:01.980 --> 28:05.746
"A man wants to build a home for his wife.

28:05.817 --> 28:08.115
He loves his wife.

28:08.186 --> 28:11.622
The house must be strong
to keep them safe."

28:13.291 --> 28:15.452
Issa, that is amazing.

28:16.628 --> 28:19.153
To be able to do that this quickly?

28:20.999 --> 28:23.331
It's truly excellent.

28:43.321 --> 28:45.414
Sometimes, I swear to God...

28:45.490 --> 28:47.822
people are their own worst enemy.

28:47.892 --> 28:50.190
<i>Yeah, tell me about it.</i>

28:50.261 --> 28:52.320
What are you doing, Saul?
You sound kind of-

28:52.397 --> 28:55.491
What do we know about Walker?
We know he's a sniper.

28:55.567 --> 28:57.330
Snipers are trained to go to ground...

28:57.402 --> 29:00.496
either in plain sight or,
as is the case here...

29:00.572 --> 29:02.335
that doesn't work...

29:02.407 --> 29:04.773
<i>they blend into the wild.</i>

29:04.843 --> 29:07.073
I think the other word
for that is "disappear."

29:07.145 --> 29:09.010
Hold on a second.

29:11.282 --> 29:12.772
Hello.

29:12.851 --> 29:16.309
Carrie, this is Zahira.

29:16.387 --> 29:19.322
<i>Can you meet me in 15 minutes?</i>

29:19.390 --> 29:21.858
Yeah, of course.

29:39.377 --> 29:40.867
Hey there.

29:40.945 --> 29:42.845
Whoa. Whoa. I come in peace.

29:44.649 --> 29:46.981
My bad. I didn't mean to
sneak up on you like that.

29:47.051 --> 29:49.952
- Don't worry about it.
- May I?

29:50.021 --> 29:52.046
Sure.

29:52.123 --> 29:55.650
That sure is some
work of art you got there.

29:55.727 --> 29:58.662
What is that, some sort of limited,
made-to-measure edition?

29:58.730 --> 30:00.197
Something like that.

30:02.767 --> 30:05.497
- Nice. What you hunting?
- Office supplies.

30:05.570 --> 30:08.698
What you got there?

30:08.773 --> 30:11.367
Marlin 336 with a Vari-X.

30:11.442 --> 30:14.343
- Yeah. Gets the job done.
- Oh, it'll get her done.

30:15.814 --> 30:17.645
It sure is a beautiful day for it.

30:17.715 --> 30:19.876
You, uh- You have yourself a good one.

30:19.951 --> 30:21.885
Want to see this thing in action?

30:21.953 --> 30:23.682
Just about got it in the sweet spot.

30:25.056 --> 30:27.081
Sure. Sure. Why-Why not?

30:51.049 --> 30:52.880
I didn't get your name.

30:52.951 --> 30:55.476
It's, uh, Dan.

30:55.553 --> 30:57.282
Name's Dan.

30:57.355 --> 30:59.414
Good talking to you, Dan.

30:59.490 --> 31:01.424
Good luck out there.

31:01.492 --> 31:04.052
Right. Y-You too.

31:11.536 --> 31:13.367
Hello, Zahira.

31:13.438 --> 31:15.269
When you came to our home...

31:15.340 --> 31:20.368
you knew it was not permitted
for you to be alone with my husband.

31:20.445 --> 31:23.778
Two pairs of ears to hear what you had
to say being better than one.

31:25.416 --> 31:26.508
Maybe.

31:27.552 --> 31:29.679
I love my husband, Carrie.

31:29.754 --> 31:33.349
- He's a good man.
- I don't doubt it.

31:39.764 --> 31:45.225
I understand what you said about
this country- the knife edge it's on.

31:45.303 --> 31:46.930
Please.

31:47.005 --> 31:50.236
I need your word that
you will not say anything...

31:50.308 --> 31:52.299
to anyone about our meeting.

31:52.377 --> 31:54.641
You have it.

31:57.215 --> 31:59.183
This man Walker-

31:59.250 --> 32:03.346
over the last few weeks,
he has come to the mosque maybe...

32:03.421 --> 32:05.548
eight or nine times.

32:05.623 --> 32:09.787
Every time he meets with a man
who does not come to the mosque to pray.

32:09.861 --> 32:12.329
Just to do business.

32:12.397 --> 32:14.194
Do you know the name of this man?

32:15.600 --> 32:19.730
All I know is he drives a car
with the diplomatic plates.

32:20.471 --> 32:21.961
Which country?

32:25.143 --> 32:26.667
S-Saudi Arabia.

32:29.347 --> 32:30.837
Thank you.

32:58.910 --> 33:00.707
Bad dream?

33:00.778 --> 33:02.746
Yeah.

33:02.814 --> 33:04.907
Yeah, it was.

33:10.188 --> 33:12.179
Hey, what you got there?

33:16.594 --> 33:19.495
Hey, this is beautiful, Issa.

33:19.564 --> 33:21.555
This is really great.

33:24.535 --> 33:26.469
Thank you.

33:44.622 --> 33:47.420
What is this? What's going on?

34:19.489 --> 34:21.617
<i>Nicholas?</i>

34:22.760 --> 34:25.159
<i>Can you hear me, Nicholas?</i>

34:25.228 --> 34:27.219
<i>Nicholas.</i>

34:29.766 --> 34:32.167
Yeah, I can hear you.

34:32.235 --> 34:33.965
<i>You're angry.</i>

34:34.038 --> 34:36.370
How the fuck do you think I feel?

34:37.308 --> 34:39.367
<i>You're also in shock.</i>

34:41.411 --> 34:45.143
<i>Which is why you told our friend in</i>
<i>Washington to tell me that it's all over.</i>

34:45.216 --> 34:50.244
I've been living the last eight years
thinking I killed Tom Walker...

34:50.321 --> 34:52.516
which I now find out is not true.

34:52.590 --> 34:55.684
Which means everything I did-
everything-

34:55.760 --> 34:58.354
<i>Is the peace you found</i>
<i>in Islam a false peace?</i>

34:58.429 --> 35:00.329
Everything I believed in.

35:00.398 --> 35:04.596
<i>You believed in Allah's forgiveness and,</i>
<i>through Allah's mercy, in yourself.</i>

35:04.669 --> 35:06.466
It was all a trick.

35:06.537 --> 35:08.402
It was based on a lie.

35:08.473 --> 35:11.533
<i>I did not let you</i>
<i>actually kill your friend.</i>

35:12.410 --> 35:14.742
<i>Isn't that good news?</i>

35:23.421 --> 35:25.412
What is Walker doing?

35:27.024 --> 35:28.389
<i>Helping.</i>

35:28.459 --> 35:30.256
<i>That's all you need to know.</i>

35:33.998 --> 35:36.262
<i>You remember the new beginning</i>
<i>you were given?</i>

35:36.334 --> 35:38.859
Yes. I remember.

35:38.936 --> 35:40.528
<i>Issa.</i>

35:43.441 --> 35:46.001
You trusted me with Issa.

35:46.077 --> 35:47.374
Why?

35:47.445 --> 35:50.414
<i>Why not trust a man</i>
<i>who would rather die...</i>

35:50.481 --> 35:52.506
<i>than give information to his enemy?</i>

35:52.583 --> 35:56.178
You got your enemy to teach your own son.

35:56.254 --> 36:00.213
<i>No, we only began as enemies...</i>

36:00.291 --> 36:03.055
<i>because that's what others told us to be.</i>

36:04.295 --> 36:06.388
<i>Are we enemies now?</i>

36:09.967 --> 36:12.265
<i>Have you forgotten?</i>

36:17.708 --> 36:20.677
Buy me some peanuts...

36:20.745 --> 36:23.236
and Cracker Jack.

36:23.314 --> 36:27.148
I don't care...

36:27.218 --> 36:29.948
- if I never get back.
- Get back.

36:30.021 --> 36:34.788
I want to root, root, root for-

36:34.859 --> 36:36.724
For the home team.

36:38.429 --> 36:42.092
Finish it. Come on, brat.
You're almost done.

36:42.166 --> 36:47.297
Let me root, root, root for the home team.

36:47.371 --> 36:50.966
If they don't win, it's a shame.

36:51.042 --> 36:55.502
For it's one, two,
three strikes, you're out...

36:55.580 --> 36:59.607
at the old ball game.

37:02.787 --> 37:04.618
You a brat.

37:04.689 --> 37:08.591
- You <i>are</i> a brat.
- You <i>are</i> a brat.

37:08.659 --> 37:10.820
And you're gonna be late for school.
Get out of here.

37:16.867 --> 37:20.303
Hey. Are you forgetting something?

37:21.706 --> 37:23.799
Score a goal today.

37:38.756 --> 37:40.280
Issa!

37:40.358 --> 37:42.383
...Issa?

37:42.460 --> 37:44.758
... Issa?

37:45.563 --> 37:47.053
Issa!

37:49.166 --> 37:50.929
Issa!

37:51.002 --> 37:52.993
Mama!

37:54.705 --> 37:56.468
Issa!

37:58.609 --> 38:01.737
Issa!

38:26.070 --> 38:28.595
Issa!

38:39.817 --> 38:41.284
Issa?

38:49.927 --> 38:51.792
Issa?

38:52.663 --> 38:54.995
Issa.

38:55.066 --> 38:56.556
Issa?

38:56.634 --> 38:58.864
Issa.

39:01.572 --> 39:03.938
Issa.

39:08.946 --> 39:11.380
Issa!

40:57.188 --> 40:59.452
<i>Allahu Akbar.</i>

40:59.523 --> 41:01.457
<i>Allahu Akbar.</i>

41:07.865 --> 41:10.493
<i>I pray every day...</i>

41:10.568 --> 41:14.402
<i>that you never lose sight of what you</i>
<i>committed to do in Issa's name.</i>

41:17.308 --> 41:21.005
<i>I never wanted or planned any of this.</i>

41:21.078 --> 41:26.015
<i>It was your choice- doing what you are</i>
<i>doing after what happened that day.</i>

41:27.618 --> 41:29.245
<i>But...</i>

41:30.421 --> 41:32.651
<i>in the end, you are...</i>

41:33.390 --> 41:35.585
<i>a soldier, as you say.</i>

41:37.495 --> 41:40.157
<i>And you will either</i>
<i>stay truthful to that...</i>

41:40.231 --> 41:42.199
<i>and do what you feel is right...</i>

41:43.000 --> 41:45.195
<i>or you will not.</i>

41:46.604 --> 41:48.538
Alhamdulillah.

41:52.510 --> 41:54.569
Nazir?

41:54.645 --> 41:56.169
Nazir?

42:03.554 --> 42:06.955
Nazir said that you would remember this
from two years ago.

42:09.460 --> 42:11.428
<i>At 4:42 p.m. Local time...</i>

42:11.495 --> 42:14.328
<i>a drone missile hit and destroyed</i>
<i>part of a compound...</i>

42:14.398 --> 42:16.423
<i>120 miles northeast of Mosul...</i>

42:16.500 --> 42:18.400
<i>in the mountains of northern Iraq...</i>

42:18.469 --> 42:21.632
<i>from which Abu Nazir,</i>
<i>the leader of the I.P.L.A...</i>

42:21.705 --> 42:23.673
<i>is believed to have been operating.</i>

42:23.741 --> 42:27.177
<i>The images being broadcast</i>
<i>on some news outlets around the world...</i>

42:27.244 --> 42:31.237
<i>of the bodies of 83 dead children</i>
<i>allegedly killed in the strike...</i>

42:31.315 --> 42:33.647
<i>we believe to be false...</i>

42:33.717 --> 42:36.242
<i>created by the terrorists</i>
<i>for propaganda purposes.</i>

42:37.288 --> 42:40.018
And they call us terrorists.

42:40.090 --> 42:43.856
<i>...all that can be done</i>
<i>is done to protect the innocent.</i>

42:45.362 --> 42:48.456
<i>Make no mistake-</i>
<i>that in the planning of these missions...</i>

42:48.532 --> 42:52.024
<i>all that can be done is done</i>
<i>to protect the innocent...</i>

42:52.102 --> 42:55.833
<i>in particular,</i>
<i>the precious lives of children...</i>

42:55.906 --> 42:59.808
<i>while we keep our promise to hunt down</i>
<i>the terrorists who continue to plot against-</i>

43:02.079 --> 43:04.343
As you already know,
that man there, the vice president...

43:04.415 --> 43:08.374
is the former director of the C.I.A.
And the man most instrumental...

43:08.452 --> 43:10.682
in the drone attack
that killed young Issa.

43:10.754 --> 43:13.814
As he prepares to become president...

43:13.891 --> 43:16.792
he's going to want to use you,
to be seen with you...

43:16.860 --> 43:19.454
his American hero, more and more.

43:19.530 --> 43:21.054
Let him.

43:21.131 --> 43:23.531
We also believe that...

43:23.601 --> 43:27.037
he's going to ask you
to run for political office.

43:27.104 --> 43:30.232
Say yes. This will be
a signal to Abu Nazir...

43:30.307 --> 43:33.799
that you are committed
still to doing this.

43:52.930 --> 43:55.228
Oh, Jesus.

44:15.219 --> 44:17.449
The doctor says you should
take these with food.

44:22.526 --> 44:25.654
Go out the back way. Take a right.

44:25.729 --> 44:29.756
Your car is across the street.
The groceries are inside.

45:22.052 --> 45:23.178
Ow.

45:40.771 --> 45:44.138
That's it on the left,
home of our Saudi diplomat.

45:47.544 --> 45:49.603
Diplomatic fucking immunity.

45:49.680 --> 45:51.511
Just like Klaus in '03.

45:51.582 --> 45:54.779
That was the Swiss embassy in Caracas,
and we nearly let Klaus slip away.

45:54.852 --> 45:57.286
I'm not losing this guy, Saul.

45:58.622 --> 46:00.783
For now, we wait and see
if Mr. Zahrani does anything...

46:00.858 --> 46:03.588
or goes anywhere
that'll help us get to Walker.

46:03.660 --> 46:05.787
You live for this shit.

46:07.865 --> 46:09.856
So I've been told.

46:18.642 --> 46:22.373
What if Mr. Zahrani doesn't give us
anything anytime soon?

46:22.446 --> 46:26.177
We figure out an elegant way
to lift and interrogate him.

46:50.073 --> 46:52.303
I'm not gonna ask you
where you've been all day.

46:52.376 --> 46:55.243
I know you have a lot on your mind
and a lot to process...

46:55.312 --> 46:57.337
and I'm in danger
of sounding like a broken record-

46:57.414 --> 47:00.008
Oh, my God. What happened?

47:00.083 --> 47:02.313
- I got mugged.
- What do you mean, mugged?

47:02.386 --> 47:05.219
As in attacked and robbed.

47:05.289 --> 47:09.919
- Are you all right? Did you call the cops?
- What good are the cops gonna do?

47:09.993 --> 47:13.485
By the time I came round,
the fuckers that did this were long gone.

47:13.564 --> 47:18.968
- Where did this happen?
- Grocery store parking lot.
Three of the bastards.

47:19.036 --> 47:21.027
I-I'm fine. I'm fine.

47:21.104 --> 47:24.267
I went to the, uh-
I went to the emergency room.

47:24.341 --> 47:26.571
- Why didn't you call me?
- They got my phone.

47:26.643 --> 47:29.737
I didn't want to worry you and the kids.

47:29.813 --> 47:32.873
Seriously, it's no big deal.

47:32.950 --> 47:35.714
- Are you hurt?
- Ah, a couple broken ribs.

47:35.786 --> 47:39.745
It- Hey, hey. I'm fine. I'm fine.

47:39.823 --> 47:42.587
All right?

47:42.659 --> 47:45.492
Fuck, Brody.
You should've called the cops.

47:45.562 --> 47:48.429
Well, I really don't need
the attention right now.

47:48.498 --> 47:50.762
What else did they take?

47:50.834 --> 47:53.667
Oh, a few bucks, my pride.

47:55.239 --> 47:57.400
Well, you're all right.
That's what's important.

47:57.474 --> 47:59.203
Mm-hmm.

47:59.276 --> 48:02.268
You know what the worst part of it is?

48:02.346 --> 48:05.611
I really wanted to spend the day
with you and the kids.

48:08.018 --> 48:10.885
I want us to spend more time together-

48:10.954 --> 48:12.979
as a family.

48:13.056 --> 48:15.547
That sounds so good.

48:22.566 --> 48:26.297
Eight years out there, I come back,
I get mugged outside the grocery store.

48:26.370 --> 48:28.998
It's unbelievable.

48:29.072 --> 48:31.836
America's a violent country.
What can I tell you?

48:34.077 --> 48:36.170
Oh.

48:36.246 --> 48:39.147
- I'm sorry. Oh. And guess what.
- What?

48:39.216 --> 48:41.184
There's a message on the voice mail-

48:41.251 --> 48:43.242
from the vice president's office.

